Purpose - Fix the Simplescreenrecorder missing status icon in Fedora 32 tray

Pre-requsite -
Fedora 32 installed

Simplescreenrecorder is a package provided by RPM Fusion repository. This package is used basically for screen recordings.

For Fedora 32 the latest package that is availble as per the repository is as given below.

URL - http://download1.rpmfusion.org/free/fedora/updates/32/x86_64/s/
Package - simplescreenrecorder-0.4.2-3.fc32.x86_64.rpm

Currently i have the above package installed on my Fedora 32 system.

[admin@fed32 yum.repos.d]$ rpm -qa | grep simplescreenrecorder
simplescreenrecorder-0.4.2-3.fc32.x86_64

The issue with the currently installed package is whenever i am trying to start/stop or pause a recording it is not able to show the correct status icons in system for start, stop or pause the recording as shown in the screenshot below.

This bug is not present in the Fedora 31 system wherein the system tray icon is able to show the correct status of the recording with which it will be easy to use shortcuts to take appropriate actions (ie. whether to start, stop or pause the recording)

Lets try to understand and fix this tray icon status issue here in this article.


SimpleScreenRecorder comes a default set of icons to show the correct status of the Recorder in the System tray at the bottom right corner. Lets dig into the simplescreenrecorder rpm package to know where those icons are available on the filesystem after we install the simplescreenrecorder package.

As you could see from the below output there are .png files available for each status of recorder (ie. error, idle, paused, recording and default icon). These 5 icon status images are available in various pixel sizes in separate folder (ie. 16x16, 22x22, 24x24)

[root@fed32 ~]# rpm -ql simplescreenrecorder | grep icons
